{With 17 points you need to indicate a better than minimum opening. You have no singletons and just a 5-card trump suit so you bid 3NT. Partner says 4\D and it is your bid again. 

Partner's 4\D bid shows first round control (surely the Ace). You bid 4\H, showing your first round control. Partner now says 4NT.  

You are being Blackwooded, and with three Aces you reply 5\S. That was apparently just what North wanted to hear, so he bid 7\S.}

